{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018DDqz12txRzTy3MKnFxeyx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive summary of the Lord of the RNGs frontend components.\n\n## Summary: Lord of the RNGs Frontend Components\n\n### File Structure\nThe Lord of the RNGs feature is located at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/` with the following organization:\n\n```\nlord-of-rngs/\n├── components/\n│   ├── ActiveRoundView.tsx\n│   ├── CountdownTimer.tsx\n│   ├── TierLobby.tsx\n│   ├── TierRoundView.tsx\n│   ├── WheelVisualization.tsx\n│   └── index.ts\n├── context/\n│   └── LordOfRngsContext.tsx\n├── utils/\n│   ├── chain.ts\n│   ├── odds.ts\n│   └── mock-simulation.ts\n├── types.ts\n└── index.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Context: LordOfRngsContext.tsx**\n\nThis is the central state management for the Lord of the RNGs game. It provides:\n\n**Available Data:**\n- `activeRound: Round | null` - Currently active round (null if in lobby)\n- `tierStatuses: TierStatus[]` - Status of all 6 tiers with current rounds\n- `selectedTier: Tier | null` - User's selected tier for joining\n- `entryCount: number` - Number of entries user wants to buy\n- Various loading states: `loading`, `joining`, `buyingMore`, `claiming`, `spinning`\n- `error: string | null` - User-friendly error messages\n\n**VRF/Round State Data:**\n- Polls active round every 5 seconds (or every 15 seconds in lobby)\n- Watches for phase transitions: `waiting` → `countdown` → `spinning` → `revealing` → `complete`\n- Auto-detects when VRF is fulfilled and round enters `revealing` phase\n- Auto-claims payout for the winner after 5 seconds\n- Auto-returns losers to lobby after 3 seconds\n\n**Key Actions:**\n- `joinTierRound()` - Create or join a round\n- `buyMoreEntriesAction(entries)` - Add entries to existing round\n- `startSpin()` - Trigger VRF (permissionless, any player)\n- `claimPayout()` - Winner claims 97% of pool\n- `leaveRound()` - Return to tier lobby\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Round Data Types: types.ts**\n\n```typescript\ntype RoundPhase = \"waiting\" | \"countdown\" | \"spinning\" | \"revealing\" | \"complete\"\n\ninterface Round {\n  id: string;\n  tier: Tier;\n  entryAmount: number; // SOL per entry\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n  \n  // Players & entries\n  players: PlayerEntry[]; // Array with address, entries count, color\n  totalEntries: number;\n  poolAmount: number; // Total SOL in pool\n  \n  // Timing (in milliseconds)\n  createdAt: number;\n  countdownStartedAt?: number;\n  countdownEndsAt?: number;\n  completedAt?: number;\n  \n  // VRF & Fairness Data\n  seedHash: string;      // SHA-256 hash (shown before spin)\n  serverSeed?: string;   // Revealed after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string;     // VRF proof for on-chain verification\n  blockHash?: string;    // Blockhash used as entropy\n  \n  // Result (after spin)\n  winningSlot?: number;  // 0-indexed slot in the wheel\n  winner?: string;       // Winner's address\n  payoutAmount?: number; // 97% of pool\n  claimed?: boolean;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **ActiveRoundView.tsx**\n\nThis component displays an active round that the player is in. It shows:\n\n**Layout:**\n- Back button to return to tier lobby\n- Phase message or countdown timer (only during non-reveal phases)\n- WheelVisualization component\n\n**Props:**\n```typescript\ninterface ActiveRoundViewProps {\n  round: Round;\n  currentUserAddress: string;\n  onBackToTiers?: () => void;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Notes:**\n- Does NOT have a fairness/sidebar section\n- Focuses on the wheel animation and phase display\n- Hides messages during `revealing` and `complete` phases\n\n---\n\n### 4. **WheelVisualization.tsx**\n\nThis is the main visual component showing the spinning wheel with all player slots.\n\n**Features:**\n- **Infinite horizontal scroll** of player slots (responsive: 4-6 visible slots)\n- **Slot rendering**: One slot per entry, with player avatars and names\n- **Animations**:\n  - Slow continuous scroll during `waiting` and `countdown` phases\n  - 5-second spin animation during `spinning` phase with custom easing (fast start, dramatic deceleration)\n  - Lands exactly on winning slot during `revealing`/`complete`\n- **Golden Arrow Indicator** (\"THE ONE\") pointing down to the winning slot\n- **Winner announcement** with star and coin burst animations for `revealing` and `complete` phases\n- **Legend section** showing all players sorted by odds with:\n  - Avatar\n  - Entry count\n  - Probability percentage (calculated to sum exactly to 100%)\n\n**Winner Calculation:**\n- Iterates through players in order, accumulating entries\n- Finds which player owns the `winningSlot` index\n- Displayed with highlighted styling and \"YOU WON!\" message if current user\n\n**Performance Optimizations:**\n- Virtualization during `waiting`/`countdown` (only renders visible + buffer slots)\n- Full rendering during `spinning`/`revealing`/`complete` (needed for smooth animation)\n- Memoized components (WheelSlot, LegendItem) to prevent unnecessary re-renders\n- 7x repetition of slots for infinite scroll illusion\n\n---\n\n### 5. **TierLobby.tsx**\n\nShows a grid of 6 tier cards for the player to select and join.\n\n**Tier Card Displays:**\n- Tier name with gem icon\n- Entry amount (SOL)\n- Current round stats: **Players**, **Pool** (SOL), **Entries**\n- Phase label or countdown timer (if countdown phase)\n- Selection highlight when clicked\n\n**No fairness information** on tier cards.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **CountdownTimer.tsx**\n\nSimple countdown display used in tier cards and phase display.\n\n**Features:**\n- Shows `MM:SS` format\n- Optional label \"until reveal\"\n- Visual urgency styling when ≤10 seconds or ≤5 seconds\n- Calls `onComplete` callback when countdown reaches zero\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Chain Integration: chain.ts**\n\nHandles all on-chain interaction including VRF state detection:\n\n**Key Functions for VRF/Fairness:**\n- `readVrfRandomness(connection, vrfRequestKey)` - Reads 32 bytes of VRF randomness from Orao account\n- `deriveWinnerFromVrf(randomness, data)` - Deterministically selects winning slot from VRF bytes:\n  ```typescript\n  winningSlot = BigUint64LE(randomness[0:8]) % totalEntries\n  ```\n- `fetchRound()` - Detects if phase is `locked` (VRF requested), checks if randomness is fulfilled, upgrades to `revealing` if it is\n- `onChainRoundToUI()` - Converts on-chain phase variants to UI phases:\n  - `waiting` → \"waiting\"\n  - `active` → \"countdown\"\n  - `locked` → \"spinning\" (upgraded to \"revealing\" if VRF fulfilled)\n  - `settled` → \"complete\"\n\n**VRF Proof Storage:**\n- `seedHash` field = `vrfRequestKey.toBase58()` (the VRF request public key)\n- `vrfProof` = same as seedHash when phase is settled\n- Actual randomness bytes stored in Orao account (not in round data)\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Odds Calculation: odds.ts**\n\nCalculates win probability for each player:\n\n```typescript\ncalculateOdds(players, totalEntries, decimals=1): PlayerOdds[]\n```\n\nUses **largest remainder method** to ensure percentages sum to exactly 100%:\n1. Calculate raw percentages\n2. Floor all values\n3. Distribute remaining units to players with largest remainders\n4. Returns `{ address, entries, percentage, rawPercentage }`\n\nDisplayed in WheelVisualization legend sorted by entries (descending).\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations About Fairness\n\n**What's Currently Missing (No Sidebar/Fairness Section):**\n1. ❌ No display of `seedHash` before spin\n2. ❌ No server seed reveal after settlement\n3. ❌ No VRF proof verification UI\n4. ❌ No blockhash display\n5. ❌ No fairness explanation/education section\n\n**What's Ready:**\n1. ✅ All data fields exist in Round type (`seedHash`, `serverSeed`, `vrfProof`, `blockHash`)\n2. ✅ VRF state is properly tracked and detected via `readVrfRandomness()`\n3. ✅ Winner derivation is deterministic and verifiable\n4. ✅ Phase transitions are correct\n5. ✅ Odds are mathematically sound and displayed\n\n**To Add Fairness UI:**\nWould need to:\n1. Create a new `FairnessSection` component\n2. Display in `ActiveRoundView` (sidebar or below wheel)\n3. Show `seedHash` during `waiting`/`countdown`/`spinning`\n4. Show `vrfProof` + `serverSeed` during `revealing`/`complete`\n5. Add verification explanation text\n\n---\n\n### File Paths (Absolute)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/context/LordOfRngsContext.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/components/ActiveRoundView.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/components/WheelVisualization.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/types.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/chain.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/odds.ts`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aefe88a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59112\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 48263</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"460d6ed6-55a6-44c8-8f2f-a24854f1a42b","uuid":"53723bd0-41b0-4111-9eee-be7788c2b038","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read all Lord of the RNGs frontend component files. I need to understand:\n1. What components exist in `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/`\n2. What the ActiveRoundView shows (particularly any sidebar/fairness section)\n3. The context (LordOfRngsContext.tsx) - particularly what data is available about VRF/round state\n\nList all files in the lord-of-rngs feature directory and read the key component files.","agentId":"aefe88a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive summary of the Lord of the RNGs frontend components.\n\n## Summary: Lord of the RNGs Frontend Components\n\n### File Structure\nThe Lord of the RNGs feature is located at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/` with the following organization:\n\n```\nlord-of-rngs/\n├── components/\n│   ├── ActiveRoundView.tsx\n│   ├── CountdownTimer.tsx\n│   ├── TierLobby.tsx\n│   ├── TierRoundView.tsx\n│   ├── WheelVisualization.tsx\n│   └── index.ts\n├── context/\n│   └── LordOfRngsContext.tsx\n├── utils/\n│   ├── chain.ts\n│   ├── odds.ts\n│   └── mock-simulation.ts\n├── types.ts\n└── index.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Context: LordOfRngsContext.tsx**\n\nThis is the central state management for the Lord of the RNGs game. It provides:\n\n**Available Data:**\n- `activeRound: Round | null` - Currently active round (null if in lobby)\n- `tierStatuses: TierStatus[]` - Status of all 6 tiers with current rounds\n- `selectedTier: Tier | null` - User's selected tier for joining\n- `entryCount: number` - Number of entries user wants to buy\n- Various loading states: `loading`, `joining`, `buyingMore`, `claiming`, `spinning`\n- `error: string | null` - User-friendly error messages\n\n**VRF/Round State Data:**\n- Polls active round every 5 seconds (or every 15 seconds in lobby)\n- Watches for phase transitions: `waiting` → `countdown` → `spinning` → `revealing` → `complete`\n- Auto-detects when VRF is fulfilled and round enters `revealing` phase\n- Auto-claims payout for the winner after 5 seconds\n- Auto-returns losers to lobby after 3 seconds\n\n**Key Actions:**\n- `joinTierRound()` - Create or join a round\n- `buyMoreEntriesAction(entries)` - Add entries to existing round\n- `startSpin()` - Trigger VRF (permissionless, any player)\n- `claimPayout()` - Winner claims 97% of pool\n- `leaveRound()` - Return to tier lobby\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Round Data Types: types.ts**\n\n```typescript\ntype RoundPhase = \"waiting\" | \"countdown\" | \"spinning\" | \"revealing\" | \"complete\"\n\ninterface Round {\n  id: string;\n  tier: Tier;\n  entryAmount: number; // SOL per entry\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n  \n  // Players & entries\n  players: PlayerEntry[]; // Array with address, entries count, color\n  totalEntries: number;\n  poolAmount: number; // Total SOL in pool\n  \n  // Timing (in milliseconds)\n  createdAt: number;\n  countdownStartedAt?: number;\n  countdownEndsAt?: number;\n  completedAt?: number;\n  \n  // VRF & Fairness Data\n  seedHash: string;      // SHA-256 hash (shown before spin)\n  serverSeed?: string;   // Revealed after settlement\n  vrfProof?: string;     // VRF proof for on-chain verification\n  blockHash?: string;    // Blockhash used as entropy\n  \n  // Result (after spin)\n  winningSlot?: number;  // 0-indexed slot in the wheel\n  winner?: string;       // Winner's address\n  payoutAmount?: number; // 97% of pool\n  claimed?: boolean;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **ActiveRoundView.tsx**\n\nThis component displays an active round that the player is in. It shows:\n\n**Layout:**\n- Back button to return to tier lobby\n- Phase message or countdown timer (only during non-reveal phases)\n- WheelVisualization component\n\n**Props:**\n```typescript\ninterface ActiveRoundViewProps {\n  round: Round;\n  currentUserAddress: string;\n  onBackToTiers?: () => void;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Notes:**\n- Does NOT have a fairness/sidebar section\n- Focuses on the wheel animation and phase display\n- Hides messages during `revealing` and `complete` phases\n\n---\n\n### 4. **WheelVisualization.tsx**\n\nThis is the main visual component showing the spinning wheel with all player slots.\n\n**Features:**\n- **Infinite horizontal scroll** of player slots (responsive: 4-6 visible slots)\n- **Slot rendering**: One slot per entry, with player avatars and names\n- **Animations**:\n  - Slow continuous scroll during `waiting` and `countdown` phases\n  - 5-second spin animation during `spinning` phase with custom easing (fast start, dramatic deceleration)\n  - Lands exactly on winning slot during `revealing`/`complete`\n- **Golden Arrow Indicator** (\"THE ONE\") pointing down to the winning slot\n- **Winner announcement** with star and coin burst animations for `revealing` and `complete` phases\n- **Legend section** showing all players sorted by odds with:\n  - Avatar\n  - Entry count\n  - Probability percentage (calculated to sum exactly to 100%)\n\n**Winner Calculation:**\n- Iterates through players in order, accumulating entries\n- Finds which player owns the `winningSlot` index\n- Displayed with highlighted styling and \"YOU WON!\" message if current user\n\n**Performance Optimizations:**\n- Virtualization during `waiting`/`countdown` (only renders visible + buffer slots)\n- Full rendering during `spinning`/`revealing`/`complete` (needed for smooth animation)\n- Memoized components (WheelSlot, LegendItem) to prevent unnecessary re-renders\n- 7x repetition of slots for infinite scroll illusion\n\n---\n\n### 5. **TierLobby.tsx**\n\nShows a grid of 6 tier cards for the player to select and join.\n\n**Tier Card Displays:**\n- Tier name with gem icon\n- Entry amount (SOL)\n- Current round stats: **Players**, **Pool** (SOL), **Entries**\n- Phase label or countdown timer (if countdown phase)\n- Selection highlight when clicked\n\n**No fairness information** on tier cards.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **CountdownTimer.tsx**\n\nSimple countdown display used in tier cards and phase display.\n\n**Features:**\n- Shows `MM:SS` format\n- Optional label \"until reveal\"\n- Visual urgency styling when ≤10 seconds or ≤5 seconds\n- Calls `onComplete` callback when countdown reaches zero\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Chain Integration: chain.ts**\n\nHandles all on-chain interaction including VRF state detection:\n\n**Key Functions for VRF/Fairness:**\n- `readVrfRandomness(connection, vrfRequestKey)` - Reads 32 bytes of VRF randomness from Orao account\n- `deriveWinnerFromVrf(randomness, data)` - Deterministically selects winning slot from VRF bytes:\n  ```typescript\n  winningSlot = BigUint64LE(randomness[0:8]) % totalEntries\n  ```\n- `fetchRound()` - Detects if phase is `locked` (VRF requested), checks if randomness is fulfilled, upgrades to `revealing` if it is\n- `onChainRoundToUI()` - Converts on-chain phase variants to UI phases:\n  - `waiting` → \"waiting\"\n  - `active` → \"countdown\"\n  - `locked` → \"spinning\" (upgraded to \"revealing\" if VRF fulfilled)\n  - `settled` → \"complete\"\n\n**VRF Proof Storage:**\n- `seedHash` field = `vrfRequestKey.toBase58()` (the VRF request public key)\n- `vrfProof` = same as seedHash when phase is settled\n- Actual randomness bytes stored in Orao account (not in round data)\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Odds Calculation: odds.ts**\n\nCalculates win probability for each player:\n\n```typescript\ncalculateOdds(players, totalEntries, decimals=1): PlayerOdds[]\n```\n\nUses **largest remainder method** to ensure percentages sum to exactly 100%:\n1. Calculate raw percentages\n2. Floor all values\n3. Distribute remaining units to players with largest remainders\n4. Returns `{ address, entries, percentage, rawPercentage }`\n\nDisplayed in WheelVisualization legend sorted by entries (descending).\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations About Fairness\n\n**What's Currently Missing (No Sidebar/Fairness Section):**\n1. ❌ No display of `seedHash` before spin\n2. ❌ No server seed reveal after settlement\n3. ❌ No VRF proof verification UI\n4. ❌ No blockhash display\n5. ❌ No fairness explanation/education section\n\n**What's Ready:**\n1. ✅ All data fields exist in Round type (`seedHash`, `serverSeed`, `vrfProof`, `blockHash`)\n2. ✅ VRF state is properly tracked and detected via `readVrfRandomness()`\n3. ✅ Winner derivation is deterministic and verifiable\n4. ✅ Phase transitions are correct\n5. ✅ Odds are mathematically sound and displayed\n\n**To Add Fairness UI:**\nWould need to:\n1. Create a new `FairnessSection` component\n2. Display in `ActiveRoundView` (sidebar or below wheel)\n3. Show `seedHash` during `waiting`/`countdown`/`spinning`\n4. Show `vrfProof` + `serverSeed` during `revealing`/`complete`\n5. Add verification explanation text\n\n---\n\n### File Paths (Absolute)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/context/LordOfRngsContext.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/components/ActiveRoundView.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/components/WheelVisualization.tsx`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/types.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/chain.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/odds.ts`"}],"totalDurationMs":48263,"totalTokens":59112,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6251,"cache_read_input_tokens":50168,"output_tokens":2689,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6251,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TyBS9344B6mHss3XZr2b4E","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## Complete Fairness Verification Page Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the frontend codebase and found all the fairness-related files. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. **Fairness Page Component** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/App.tsx`)\n\nThe fairness page is defined inline as the `FairnessPage()` function (lines 891-1443). It features:\n\n**Tab Structure:**\n- **How It Works**: Educational content on two verification patterns\n- **Verify Round**: Interactive verification tools\n- **Active Seeds**: Display of current commitments\n- **History**: Recent verified rounds\n\n**Key Features:**\n\n1. **Commit-Reveal Pattern** (Crash, Close Call, Game of Trades)\n   - Server publishes SHA-256 hash of seed before betting opens\n   - Solana blockhash used as public seed (unpredictable)\n   - Server reveals seed after round\n   - Formula: `outcome = HMAC-SHA256(serverSeed, publicSeed || roundId || gameId)`\n\n2. **On-Chain VRF Pattern** (Lord of RNGs, Coinflip, Tug of Earn)\n   - Game requests randomness from VRF provider\n   - Provider generates verifiable random bytes with cryptographic proof\n   - Result stored on-chain permanently\n   - Verifiable via Solana explorer\n\n**Verification Tools:**\n- Manual seed verification with SHA-256 hashing\n- HMAC-SHA256 calculation for outcome derivation\n- Hash-to-crash-point conversion (with 1% house edge)\n- Coinflip VRF verification via claim transaction signature\n- Quick round lookup\n- Active seeds display\n- Recent rounds history table\n\n### 2. **Coinflip Verification Utility** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/verification.ts`)\n\n**Function: `verifyMatch(connection, claimTxSignature)`**\n\nVerifies fairness by:\n1. Fetching the claim transaction by signature\n2. Extracting `MatchSettled` event from program logs\n3. Reading randomness bytes from the event\n4. Re-deriving coin flip result: `firstByte % 2 === 0 ? \"heads\" : \"tails\"`\n5. Validating winner is one of creator/opponent\n6. Fetching Orao VRF account to confirm fulfillment\n\n**Returns `VerificationResult`:**\n```typescript\n{\n  verified: boolean;\n  creator: string;\n  opponent: string;\n  winner: string;\n  randomnessHex: string;\n  derivedResult: \"heads\" | \"tails\";\n  vrfFulfilled: boolean;\n}\n```\n\n### 3. **Coinflip Active Match View** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/components/ActiveMatchView.tsx`)\n\n**Verification Panel** (lines 346-390):\n- Shows after `onVerify()` completes\n- Displays: Claim TX, Randomness, Derived Result, Winner, VRF Fulfilled status\n- Link to full fairness page\n- Badge shows \"Verified\" or \"Failed\"\n\n**Props for verification:**\n```typescript\nclaimTxSignature?: string | null;\nverificationResult?: VerificationResult | null;\nverifying?: boolean;\nonVerify?: () => void;\n```\n\n### 4. **Coinflip Sidebar Fairness Info** (CoinflipPage.tsx, lines 266-298)\n\nDuring active match, shows:\n- **Match ID**: Last 8 characters\n- **Seed Hash**: First 8 + last 4 chars\n- **Server Seed** (after completion): Truncated display\n- **Block Hash** (if available): Truncated display\n\nThis is the \"Round Fairness\" section in the sidebar.\n\n### 5. **Coinflip History Modal** (CoinflipPage.tsx, lines 519-564)\n\nShows fairness data in match detail modal:\n- Match ID (full)\n- Seed Hash (full)\n- Server Seed (if revealed)\n- Block Hash (if available)\n- VRF Proof (if available)\n- Link to full fairness page verification\n\n### 6. **Lord of RNGs Fairness Display** (LordOfRngsPage.tsx)\n\nSimilar pattern to Coinflip:\n- **Sidebar fairness section** (lines 203-230)\n- **History modal** (lines 484-495)\n- Shows: Match ID, VRF Proof, Seed Hash data\n- Links to `/fairness` page\n\n### 7. **Crypto Crash Fairness** (CryptoCrashPage.tsx)\n\nSame pattern as other games - links to `/fairness` for verification\n\n### 8. **Data Types** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts`)\n\nUIMatch structure includes fairness fields:\n```typescript\nseedHash: string;        // SHA-256 hash of server seed\nserverSeed?: string;     // Revealed after settlement\nvrfProof?: string;       // VRF proof for verification\nblockHash?: string;      // Solana blockhash used\n```\n\n### **File Locations Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/src/App.tsx` (lines 891-1443) | FairnessPage component with all 4 tabs |\n| `/src/App.tsx` (lines 910-946) | SHA-256 and HMAC-SHA256 crypto functions |\n| `/src/features/coinflip/utils/verification.ts` | `verifyMatch()` function for VRF verification |\n| `/src/features/coinflip/components/ActiveMatchView.tsx` | Inline verification panel UI |\n| `/src/pages/CoinflipPage.tsx` | Sidebar fairness info & history modal |\n| `/src/pages/LordOfRngsPage.tsx` | Similar fairness display pattern |\n| `/src/pages/CryptoCrashPage.tsx` | Fairness link references |\n| `/src/pages/CloseCallPage.tsx` | Fairness link references |\n| `/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` | UIMatch fairness fields definition |\n\n### **How Fairness Works in Practice**\n\n1. **For Coinflip**: Uses on-chain VRF - randomness generated by Orao VRF provider, verified via transaction signature\n2. **For Crash/Close Call/Game of Trades**: Uses commit-reveal - server seed hash published upfront, actual seed revealed after round\n3. **Verification**: Users can input seeds/transaction signatures on `/fairness` page to independently verify outcomes\n4. **During Match**: Sidebar shows ongoing fairness commitment hashes\n5. **After Match**: Can view all fairness data in history modal or full fairness page\n\nAll files are ready for reading and contain complete implementations!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9b4a1c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 81080\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 59778</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"460d6ed6-55a6-44c8-8f2f-a24854f1a42b","uuid":"2e5cb2bf-75b3-436f-8f6a-831f8c3a971d","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read all files related to the fairness verification page in the frontend. I need to understand:\n1. The fairness page component (likely in `apps/platform/src/features/` or similar)\n2. Any existing coinflip fairness verification components\n3. How the sidebar shows VRF data in coinflip\n\nLook in:\n- `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/` for fairness-related files\n- Check both `features/coinflip/` and `features/lord-of-rngs/` directories\n- Check `pages/` or `routes/` for the fairness page route\n\nRead the key files fully and report their contents.","agentId":"a9b4a1c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## Complete Fairness Verification Page Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the frontend codebase and found all the fairness-related files. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. **Fairness Page Component** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/App.tsx`)\n\nThe fairness page is defined inline as the `FairnessPage()` function (lines 891-1443). It features:\n\n**Tab Structure:**\n- **How It Works**: Educational content on two verification patterns\n- **Verify Round**: Interactive verification tools\n- **Active Seeds**: Display of current commitments\n- **History**: Recent verified rounds\n\n**Key Features:**\n\n1. **Commit-Reveal Pattern** (Crash, Close Call, Game of Trades)\n   - Server publishes SHA-256 hash of seed before betting opens\n   - Solana blockhash used as public seed (unpredictable)\n   - Server reveals seed after round\n   - Formula: `outcome = HMAC-SHA256(serverSeed, publicSeed |